        <main>
            <section id="principles" class="mb-12 bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-4">Core Principles for Your Comeback</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">These foundational principles are crucial for a safe and effective recovery, guiding every step of your journey back to running.</p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-slate-600">
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-md">
                        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-800">1. Protect the Foot</h3>
                        <p>No weight-bearing or impact on your injured foot. Every exercise is modified for safety.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-md">
                        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-800">2. Embrace Single-Leg Work</h3>
                        <p>Your uninjured leg will become a powerhouse of strength and stability, benefiting your return to running.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-md">
                        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-800">3. Mobilize & Stabilize</h3>
                        <p>Targeting key runner's areas: hips, glutes, core, and thoracic spine to build a robust foundation.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-md">
                        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-800">4. Consistency Over Intensity</h3>
                        <p>Showing up daily is key. The cumulative effect of consistent work builds lasting resilience.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-md">
                        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-800">5. Patience is Your Pace</h3>
                        <p>Trust the process. Rushing back is the fastest route to re-injury. Be patient with your body.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-md">
                        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-800">6. Doctor's Orders</h3>
                        <p>This plan supports, but does not replace, medical advice. Stop if you feel pain and consult your doctor.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="progression-overview" class="mb-12 bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
